as long as we protect ourselves.

677
01:01:40,167 --> 01:01:42,522
Yeah, but he's braver.

678
01:01:44,367 --> 01:01:48,440
Now that you two are friends, you can go
hunt animals with my dad, right?

679
01:01:48,607 --> 01:01:50,484
So we can have real food more often.

680
01:01:50,647 --> 01:01:53,286
I think that's, uh, a good idea.

681
01:01:53,447 --> 01:01:54,846
I can help your dad hunt...

682
01:01:55,007 --> 01:01:57,123
...and, uh, you can help me
go get ammunition...

683
01:01:57,287 --> 01:02:00,484
...and other supplies in the store.
What do you think?

684
01:02:00,647 --> 01:02:03,400
I think you don't need my dad's help
to go into town.

685
01:02:07,807 --> 01:02:11,004
You, when you were a kid,
did you know how to add and subtract?

686
01:02:11,167 --> 01:02:16,116
Well, not much, heh.
I tell you what, not much now neither.

687
01:02:16,287 --> 01:02:18,676
Well, I do. My dad taught me.

688
01:02:18,847 --> 01:02:21,042
Watch. Three plus two is five.

689
01:02:21,207 --> 01:02:22,720
Six plus one is seven.

690
01:02:22,887 --> 01:02:25,276
Eight plus four is...?
Come on. It's easy.

691
01:02:25,447 --> 01:02:26,960
No counting on your fingers.

692
01:02:27,127 --> 01:02:28,560
- That's cheating.
- Heh.

693
01:02:28,967 --> 01:02:31,356
It's 12, Neighbour Patrick, 12.

694
01:02:31,527 --> 01:02:34,724
I'm glad to know
your dad is good for something.

695
01:02:37,007 --> 01:02:39,999
What about geography?
Did you know about geography?

696
01:02:40,407 --> 01:02:43,080
Let's see. In what country
is the Great Wall of China?

697
01:02:43,247 --> 01:02:45,556
Oh, gosh. Uh...

698
01:02:45,727 --> 01:02:48,400
- Mexico.
- Nope. China.

699
01:02:48,567 --> 01:02:51,206
- Do you know what language they speak?
- Uh, Chinese.

700
01:02:51,567 --> 01:02:52,966
Very good.

701
01:02:53,127 --> 01:02:55,687
- Do you know what the population is?
- Right now?

702
01:02:56,767 --> 01:02:59,156
[BOTH CHUCKLING
AND THEN LAUGHING]

703
01:02:59,327 --> 01:03:00,885
[♪♪♪]

704
01:03:02,567 --> 01:03:04,000
What is it?

705
01:03:04,207 --> 01:03:05,959
What's so funny?

706
01:03:06,127 --> 01:03:07,879
Why are you laughing?

707
01:03:08,367 --> 01:03:10,119
Oh, shit.

708
01:03:10,607 --> 01:03:13,963
Dad, he said a swear word.
If you swear, people think badly of you.

709
01:03:14,127 --> 01:03:16,243
J ACK: I know. I know.
LU: Right, Dad?

710
01:03:16,407 --> 01:03:17,840
J ACK: I know.
PATRICK: They will.

711
01:03:18,007 --> 01:03:20,157
It's important
what people think about us.

712
01:03:20,327 --> 01:03:23,524
J ACK: Yeah. Well, especially
the Chinese. Goddamn Chine...

713
01:03:23,687 --> 01:03:25,598
[LAUGHING]

714
01:03:26,007 --> 01:03:29,204
And then E.T.'s heart
started to beat again.

715
01:03:29,367 --> 01:03:32,643
Boom-boom, boom-boom,
boom-boom.

716
01:03:32,807 --> 01:03:37,039
And the plant that looked like
it was dead came back to life.

717
01:03:37,207 --> 01:03:38,526
LU:
Mm.

718
01:03:38,687 --> 01:03:40,917
That's a nice story.

719
01:03:41,087 --> 01:03:42,202
