722
01:03:52,287 --> 01:03:53,402
[CHUCKLES]

723
01:03:54,247 --> 01:03:56,477
And she's out like a light.

724
01:03:58,607 --> 01:04:01,405
- Should I take her up?
- I'll handle it.

725
01:04:05,967 --> 01:04:09,755
Another night where she goes to sleep
without brushing her teeth.

726
01:04:09,927 --> 01:04:11,838
Not a tragedy.

727
01:04:12,527 --> 01:04:15,166
J ACK:
I don't like it when she disobeys.

728
01:04:16,487 --> 01:04:19,445
It's normal. I'm sure you were rebellious
at her age too.

729
01:04:19,607 --> 01:04:22,167
It'd be normal
if we were living in a normal world.

730
01:04:22,327 --> 01:04:24,318
Disobeying is dangerous here.

731
01:04:24,487 --> 01:04:26,523
She's a lot like her mother.

732
01:04:27,207 --> 01:04:29,562
She has nothing of her father in her.

733
01:04:42,247 --> 01:04:44,397
I'm sorry about your dog, Patrick.

734
01:04:44,567 --> 01:04:47,365
- I don't know what came over me.
- It's all right, ah.

735
01:04:48,167 --> 01:04:52,797
I know what it's like to have
weird things come over you, heh.

736
01:04:54,007 --> 01:04:55,998
These things are back.

737
01:04:59,287 --> 01:05:03,599
I haven't forgotten what happened
or what you did.

738
01:05:04,607 --> 01:05:06,962
But I can't do this alone. Not with Lu.

739
01:05:07,127 --> 01:05:08,879
You can count on me.

740
01:05:09,487 --> 01:05:11,125
For anything.

741
01:05:12,407 --> 01:05:14,875
